d a huge celebrity...<br><br>so uh... yeh ^^ the big names are rich... the guys starting out are incredibly poor... (like many professions :3)  <p>.oO0 halo^2 0Oo.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/u1psychofish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>1psychofish</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/30/01 3:47:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.phishstudios.50megs.com/phishlogo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Income for Manga Artists in Japan?</span><hr size=1> Yeah it's really getting a breakthrough as an artist, but when you've had it then you'll make heaps of money nd be famous and stuff. <p><b> I am Jays Looser mentality</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugrifter730.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grifter730</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/30/01 12:43:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Takahashi</span><hr size=1> Is Rumiko Takahashi even drawing mangas still?<br><br>Also, I've never been to Japan, so I'm wondering how much mangas they produce? I mean, the US puts out so many comics each week, do the Japanese put out the same amount? I guess only the best ones make it on top eh? Personally, I love Ken Akamatsu the most. Love Hina just rocks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubboyhalohalo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bboyhalohalo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/30/01 6:30:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  hahaha</span><hr size=1> ok... let me tell you.. if you think the US makes comics.. take the US output and raise to the 10th power... that's how much comics are made in japan.. there must be rivers of ink that go into studios and back out into the tons of comic magazine monthlies...<br><br>u may say.. &quot;monthly?&quot; but.. these are 400 page + magazines.. they look like phone books... Love Hina originally appeared in such a magazine.. as do pretty much every comic that's made it big..<br><br>the comic magazines i get regularly are Ace-A and LaLa... if you go to a well-stocked japanese bookstore, you will see these and many more...<br><br>lol the first time i went to asahiya bookstore i was floored.. shelves and shelves of tankoubans and magazines and art books...<br><br>seriously.. comics are so big in japan that people have based their lifestyles on them...<br>BTW: if you like Akamatsu a lot.. he has another comic running right now called &quot;Ai Tomaranai!&quot;... Love Hina is still running also... I think he has a really big studio cuz of how high-quality his comics are.. the amount of comic toned used is simply amazing....<br><br>whew.. anyway i just wanted to emphasize that LOTS of comics are made in japan. but.. u just gotta see for yourself ^_^<br><br>p.s. if im not mistaken... &quot;Inu-yasha,&quot; by Takahashi is still running.. but i don't keep up with it very much... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugrifter730.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grifter730</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/30/01 8:46:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Ken Akamatsu</span><hr size=1> As far as I know, both Love Hina and Ai ga Tomaranai are completed. Love Hina having run through 14 volumes, and Ai ga Tomaranai ending after 9 volumes. Also, Ai ga Tomaranai was published before Love Hina I believe.<br><br>I didn't know there were THAT many comics in Japan. Goodness, I guess the competition is near impossible there eh? I wonder what the chances are of people there making it as a manga artist.<br><br>In any case, can you read Japanese or something? Since you went to a Japanese store, so I'm just wondering. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubboyhalohalo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bboyhalohalo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/1/01 5:24:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ken Akamatsu</span><hr size=1> yeh... i can read hiragana and katakana... but not enough vocabulary to translate well.. and not nearly enough kanji for that matter &gt;_&lt; <br>i get by with the scant words i know, a dictionary, and the images... <p>.oO0 halo^2 0Oo.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugrifter730.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grifter730</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/1/01 7:21:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ...</span><hr size=1> Well, if you can read Japanese, try going to www.ailove.net and see what Ken Akamatsu is up to, I think that's his web page. I wonder what he'll be doing now that he's finished with Love Hina. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubboyhalohalo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bboyhalohalo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/1/01 7:50:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ...</span><hr size=1> hmm... the news section has a bunch of Love Hina-related news... Love Hina &quot;okazaki-collection&quot; (?) release on dec 16...<br>the second point is about LH trading cards.. last point says vol 13 and Iro-Hina vol 2 were released.. LH vol 14 to come Jan 17...<br><br>nani?!.. I think &quot;Iro-Hina&quot; is the current comic right now.. since its the newest thing being released and advertised in magazines ive seen...<br><br>other than that i don't see any really new stuph...<br><br>lol check out his doujin section.. u can see his well-grounded education in hentai manga :3... <p>.oO0 halo^2 0Oo.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uejsudarthpupi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>E J Su DarthPupi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/1/01 10:46:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.protodepot.com/avatar/nia.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Takahashi</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I'm wondering how much mangas they produce? I mean, the US puts out so many comics each week, do the Japanese put out the same amount?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>6,500million books was published in Japan in 1995, of which 2,200million are comic books. another words, more than 1/3 of the book publication is comic books.<br>American comic publication is nothing compare to Japan. <p><center><i>"Talent is worthless without hard work."</i><br><b><a href="http://www.protodepot.com">Prototype Garage</a></b></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugrifter730.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grifter730</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/2/01 12:27:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Doujinshi? where?</span><hr size=1> HEYYYYY Where did you see his Doujinshi artworkkkk???? wahhhhhhh, I wanna see I wanna see!!! I wish I can read Japanese <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Volume 14 will be out in January? Well, from what I understand, the last chapter has been released. It may not have been compiled for publication, but it's been released in the magazine I think. In any case, volume 14 is the ending of Love Hina (is Iro Hina the Japanese title? I thought ai = love, does iro = love as well?), so what will he do after Love Hina?????? Man, I'm such a groupie of Akamatsu, I've even downloaded translation of his earlier manga... that Ai ga Toramanai one T_T<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugrifter730.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grifter730</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/2/01 12:33:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Doujinshi</span><hr size=1> Well, I managed to find his doujinshi work, except all I see are the covers, hehehe. Are these works of his before his works were published??? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubboyhalohalo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bboyhalohalo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/2/01 3:44:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Doujinshi</span><hr size=1> &quot;Iro-hina&quot; is not the same thing as Love Hina... but i dunno what the difference is in the actual publications.. if it's new artwork or story or what... <p>.oO0 halo^2 0Oo.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugrifter730.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grifter730</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/2/01 4:20:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   doujinshi</span><hr size=1> So are these doujinshi his unpublished works? Were you able to see more than just the covers from his site??? <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showMessage?topicID=1172.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showMessage?topicID=1146.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1159.topic&index=13><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.emailToFriend?topicID=1159.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.threadControl?topicID=1159.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1159.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1159.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub25.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="polykarbonbbsfrm18">PK-BBS Rules and Regulations!<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm3">News and Updates<option value="polykarbonbbsfrm2">Photoshop and Art quest